# Code Style — {{.ProjectName}}

## TypeScript

- Strict mode is non-negotiable: `strict: true` in tsconfig with no escape hatches
- Use `type` aliases for component props, not `interface` — interfaces invite extension, props should be explicit
- Prefer named exports over default exports everywhere (except Next.js pages/layouts which require defaults)
- Use `satisfies` for type-safe object literals instead of type assertions
- Avoid enums; use `as const` objects or string literal unions

## Components

- One component per file; file name matches component name in PascalCase
- Props type is defined directly above the component in the same file
- Destructure props in the function signature: `function Button({ variant, children }: ButtonProps)`
- Colocate hooks, helpers, and sub-components in the same file if they're only used there

## Styling

- Tailwind CSS only — no CSS modules, no styled-components, no inline `style` props
- Use `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional class composition
- Extract repeated class combinations into component variants, not utility classes
- Responsive design: mobile-first with Tailwind breakpoint prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)

## File Organization

- kebab-case for directories and non-component files
- PascalCase for component files: `UserProfile.tsx`
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) only for `components/ui/` — avoid them elsewhere to keep tree-shaking clean
